#Read qza file from male
#unweighted unifrac

male_unweigh <- read_qza("male_unweighted_unifrac_pcoa_results.qza")
fem_unweigh <- read_qza("unweighted_unifrac_pcoa_results.qza")
male_weigh <- read_qza("male_weighted_unifrac_pcoa_results.qza")
fem_weigh <- read_qza("weighted_unifrac_pcoa_results.qza")
View(male_unweigh$data)

View(fem_unweigh$data$Vectors$SampleID)

pcoa_pallete <- c("#0000FF", "#FFA500", "#FF0000", "#008000")

#PCoA with elipse for unweight male
yui <- male_unweigh$data$Vectors%>% 
  select(SampleID, PC1,PC2)%>%
  mutate(Group = gsub("[0-9]+", "", SampleID)) %>% # Create Group column by removing numbers from SampleID
  ggplot(aes(x=PC1, y=PC2, color=Group)) +
  geom_point(alpha=0.4, size = 3.0) + #alpha controls transparency and helps when points are overlapping
  xlab(paste("PC1: ", sprintf("%.2f", 100 * male_unweigh$data$ProportionExplained[1]), "%")) +
  ylab(paste("PC2: ", sprintf("%.2f", 100 *male_unweigh$data$ProportionExplained[2]), "%")) +
  theme_bw() +
  ggtitle("Unweighted UniFrac in male") + scale_colour_manual(name = "",
                                                              values = pcoa_pallete, breaks = c("MC","ME", "MB", "MEB"),
                                                              labels = c("Control", "Chronic", "Binge", "Chronic plus Binge")) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 16, face = "bold", family = "Times"),
        axis.text.y = element_text( size = 12, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.text.x = element_text( size = 12, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.title=element_text(size=14, face = "bold", colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        legend.text=element_text(size=12, family = "Times"),
        legend.title=element_text(size=14, face= "bold", family = "Times"),
        plot.margin = unit(c(5,5,5,5), "mm")) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-0.2, 0.25)) + scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-0.25, 0.3)) +
 geom_mark_ellipse(aes(color=Group),expand = unit(3, "mm")) + annotate("text", x=0.22, y=0.22, label= "p-value = 0.002",
                                                                       size= 5, family = "Times")
  
print(yui)

# Rarefaction curve for female

shanon_rarefy_fem <- read.csv("shannon_female.csv")
View(shanon_rarefy_fem)


# Melt the data into long format
data_long_fem <- shanon_rarefy_fem %>%
  gather(key = "depth", value = "shannon_index", contains("depth"))

View(data_long_fem)
# Convert depth to numeric type
# Extract the numeric part of depth values
data_long_fem$depth <- as.numeric(sub("depth\\.([0-9]+)_iter.*", "\\1", data_long_fem$depth))

pallete_curve <- c( "#00bfc4", "#11bfe2", "#11b5f7", "#50aeff", "#a39fff",
                    "#ffa500", "#d89000", "#ffc966", "#FFD580","#ffdb99", 
                    "#ff1919", "#ff6666", "#ff7f7f", "#ff9cba", "#ffbaba",
                   "#7cae00", "#39b600", "#00bb4e", "#00bf7d","#0BDA51"
                   ) 

# Plot the rarefaction curve
fem_curve <-ggplot(data_long_fem, aes(x = depth, y = shannon_index, color = sample.id)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "",
       x = "Sequencing depth",
       y = "Shannon Index") +
  theme_classic() +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0.0,6.5),
                     breaks = seq(0, 6.5, by = 0.5)) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0,11000),
                     breaks = seq(0, 11000, by = 1000)) +
scale_colour_manual(name = "Sample ID", labels = c( "FC1", "FC2", "FC3", "FC4", "FC5",
                                                    "FE1", "FE2", "FE3", "FE4", "FE5",
                                                    "FB1", "FB2", "FB3", "FB4", "FB5",
                                                     "FEB1", "FEB2", "FEB3", "FEB4", "FEB5"),
                    breaks = c("FC1", "FC2", "FC3", "FC4", "FC5",
                               "FE1", "FE2", "FE3", "FE4", "FE5",
                               "FB1", "FB2", "FB3", "FB4", "FB5",
                               "Feb-01", "Feb-02", "Feb-03", "Feb-04", "Feb-05"),
                     values = pallete_curve) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = -0.05, size = 16, face = "bold", family = "Times"),
        axis.text.y = element_text( size = 13, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.text.x = element_text( size = 13, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.title=element_text(size=15, face = "bold", colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        legend.text=element_text(size=13, family = "Times"),
        legend.title=element_text(size=15, face= "bold", family = "Times"))


print(fem_curve)

 #Rarefaction for male

shanon_rarefy_male <- read.csv("shannon.csv")
View(shanon_rarefy_male)


# Melt the data into long format
data_long_male <- shanon_rarefy_male %>%
  gather(key = "depth", value = "shannon_index", contains("depth"))

View(data_long_male)
# Convert depth to numeric type
# Extract the numeric part of depth values
data_long_male$depth <- as.numeric(sub("depth\\.([0-9]+)_iter.*", "\\1", data_long_male$depth))

# Plot the rarefaction curve for male
male_curve <-ggplot(data_long_male, aes(x = depth, y = shannon_index, color = sample.id)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "",
       x = "Sequencing depth",
       y = "Shannon Index") +
  theme_classic() +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0.0,7.0),
                     breaks = seq(0, 7.0, by = 0.5)) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0,11000),
                     breaks = seq(0, 11000, by = 1000)) +
  scale_colour_manual(name = "Sample ID", labels = c("MB1", "MB2", "MB3", "MB4", "MB5",
                                                     "MC1", "MC2", "MC3", "MC4", "MC5",
                                                     "ME1", "ME2", "ME3", "ME4", "ME5",
                                                     "MEB1", "MEB2", "MEB3", "MEB4", "MEB5"),
                      breaks = c("MC1", "MC2", "MC3", "MC4", "MC5",
                                 "ME1", "ME2", "ME3", "ME4", "ME5",
                                 "MB1", "MB2", "MB3", "MB4", "MB5",
                                 "MEB1", "MEB2", "MEB3", "MEB4", "MEB5"),
                      values = pallete_curve) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = -0.05, size = 16, face = "bold", family = "Times"),
        axis.text.y = element_text( size = 13, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.text.x = element_text( size = 13, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.title=element_text(size=15, face = "bold", colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        legend.text=element_text(size=13, family = "Times"),
        legend.title=element_text(size=15, face= "bold", family = "Times"))


print(male_curve)

ggarrange(male_curve, fem_curve,
          labels = c("A", "B"),
          nrow = 2)
